# Security Rules — aide

## Authentication & Authorization

- Authenticate every protected endpoint
- Authorize per resource — default deny
- Session/token expiry enforced server-side

## Input Validation

- Validate and sanitize all external input
- Parameterized queries — no dynamic SQL concatenation
- Escape output in UI to prevent XSS

## Secrets

- Never commit secrets, tokens, or private keys
- Use environment variables or secret manager
- Rotate credentials if accidentally exposed

## Dependencies

- Run audit on new dependencies
- Pin versions; review critical CVEs before merge

## Data Protection

- Encrypt sensitive data at rest and in transit (TLS)
- Log no PII or credentials
- Apply least-privilege for service accounts

## Prohibited

- `eval()` or dynamic code execution on user input
- Debug endpoints in production
- Security through obscurity as sole control

## Reference

- Report security issues privately to project maintainers
